					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary on the book of Numbers (fragments).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="142v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Be-midbar</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פירוש במדבר</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/305238133">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/305238133" xml:lang="en">Samuel ben Moses ha-Rofe, al-Magrebi, active 15th century </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/305238133" xml:lang="he">הרופא, שמואל בן משה המערבי</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Part of an Arabic commentary on Numbers 1:1-49, 1:50-3:40, 4:21-5:24, 5:27-6:7, 6:26-7:1, 7:12-8:5, 8:7-9:17, 9:18-11:4, 11:6-12:6, 12:8-15:41, 16:1-18:2, 18:4-32.</p>
								<p>In folios 71-134 the headings are written in red ink.</p>
								<p>Several sections of muḳadimat included in the manuscript, cf. Or 2484,<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">396</ref>. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; Oriental semi-cursive script of the 16 and 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex.</support>
								<extent>142 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height/>
										<width>135</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>133</height>
										<width>95</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>142 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Fragments of three different groups of quires, originally of 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Signatures in Hebrew letters and Arabic numerals on the upper margin of the first page of a quire (partially preserved).</p>
									<p>Imperfect at hte beginning and at the end, with lacunae throughout.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Several pages pages partially stained. </p>
									<p>Lacunae after folios 7, 19, 29, 32, 33, 40, 50, 60, 70, 106, 134.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="23 26" writtenLines="23 26">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Catchowords on every verso.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="3">
							<summary>Oriental semi-cursive script of the 16 and 17th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus from="1r" to="70v"/>, <locus from="71r" to="134v"/>, <locus from="135r" to="142v"/> - written in different but similar scripts.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
